=====================================================
                     Geomys
       A Gopher Browser for Macintosh
                   Version 0.2.0
=====================================================

Browse Gopherspace from your classic Macintosh.


About Geomys
-----------

Geomys is a Gopher protocol browser for the Apple
Macintosh Plus and later models running System 6.0.8
or later. It connects to Gopher servers over TCP/IP
using MacTCP, providing a graphical browser interface
for navigating Gopherspace.

Geomys implements RFC 1436 (The Internet Gopher
Protocol) and RFC 4266 (The gopher URI Scheme).
It supports all canonical and non-canonical Gopher
item types, including directories, text files,
search queries, and informational messages.

The browser features a web-style interface with an
address bar, back/forward/refresh/home navigation
buttons, and a status bar — all designed to follow
the Apple Human Interface Guidelines.


System Requirements
-------------------

  - Macintosh Plus or later (68000 CPU)
  - System 6.0.8 or later
  - MacTCP 2.1 (configured with a valid TCP/IP
    connection)
  - 4 MB RAM recommended
  - Network connection (Ethernet or compatible)


Getting Started
---------------

1. Make sure MacTCP is installed and configured in
   your Control Panel. You will need a working TCP/IP
   connection to your network.

2. Double-click the Geomys application to launch it.

3. Geomys opens to its home page (default:
   gopher://sdf.org). You can change the home page
   in Options > Home Page.

4. Click on directory items to navigate. Click on
   text items to read them. Use the address bar to
   enter a Gopher URL directly.

5. Use the Back and Forward buttons (or Cmd-[ and
   Cmd-]) to navigate through your browsing history.

6. To select text, click and drag in the content
   area. Double-click to select a word. Hold Shift
   and click to extend the selection. Press Cmd-C
   to copy. The address bar also supports Cut,
   Copy, and Paste via the Edit menu.

7. To quit, choose Quit from the File menu or press
   Command-Q.


Credits
-------

Geomys was created by Micheal Waltz with assistance
from Claude Code, an AI by Anthropic.

Geomys is cross-compiled on Linux using Retro68, the
68k Macintosh cross-compilation toolchain by
Wolfgang Thaller.

This project incorporates code from two open-source
classic Macintosh applications by joshua stein:

  wallops - IRC client for classic Macintosh
  MacTCP wrapper, DNS resolution, and utility
  functions are used directly from this project.

  subtext - BBS server for classic Macintosh
  Additional networking and utility code.

Both projects are released under the ISC license.

Geomys is a sibling project to Flynn, a Telnet and
Finger client for classic Macintosh. Both share
infrastructure and design patterns.


